abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/28\/surah-al-fatihah-every-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":42945,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Recitation of Surat al-Fatihah in every prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 28, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"'Ubadah ibn al-Samit reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThere is no prayer for one who does not recite the opening of the Book, Surat al-Fatihah.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 756, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 394 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25027,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/06\/28\/surah-al-fatihah-enough\/","url_meta":{"origin":42945,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Recitation: Surat al-Fatihah is enough, more is better","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 28, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ata\u2019 reported: Abu Huraira, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIn every prayer is a recitation. Prayers that were recited aloud by the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, we have recited aloud to you, and what he recited silently, we have kept silent with you. Whoever recites\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3604,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/10\/surat-al-fatihah-allah-responds\/","url_meta":{"origin":42945,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Allah responds to Surat al-Fatihah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 10, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAllah Almighty said: I have divided prayer between Myself and My servant into two halves, and My servant shall have what he has asked for. When the servant says, \u2018All praise is due to Allah, the Lord of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4288,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/05\/fajr-rakaat-light\/","url_meta":{"origin":42945,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Fajr: The Prophet would sometimes pray lightly","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would sometimes perform two cycles of prayer before the dawn prayer so lightly that I would say to myself, \"Did he recite Surat al-Fatihah?\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1165, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 724 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon)\u00a0according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35858,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/27\/surat-al-fatihah-unique\/","url_meta":{"origin":42945,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Surat al-Fatihah unlike any revealed scripture","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ubayy ibn Ka\u2019b reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said to him, \u201cHow do you recite in prayer?\u201d Ubayy said, \u201cI recite the foundation of the Book, Surat al-Fatihah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cBy the One in whose hand is my soul, nothing like it has\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35863,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/04\/27\/fatihah-baqarah-descend\/","url_meta":{"origin":42945,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Al-Fatihah and al-Baqarah descend from heaven","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: While the Angel Gabriel was sitting with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, he heard a creaking noise above him. Gabriel raised his head and he said, \u201cThis is a door of heaven that has been opened today and it has never been opened before\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/42945","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithon